# Sajtmaskin Terminology

## Site layers (top to bottom)

| Layer | What it is | URL pattern |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
| **Vercel** | Hosting platform. Deploys, domains, env vars, CDN. | vercel.com |
| **v0** | AI code generation platform. Generates React code, returns demoUrl. | v0.dev, *.vusercontent.net |
| **Sajtmaskin** | Our app. Orchestrates v0, manages projects, users, deploy flow. | sajtmaskin.se |
| **Demo sites** | User-generated sites. Built by v0, previewed via demoUrl, deployed to Vercel. | *.vercel.app or custom domain |

## Pages in our app

### Start page (`/`)

The landing page with 4 entry modes shown as tabs/cards:

| Mode | Code name | Component | What it does |
|------|-----------|-----------|-------------|
| **Analyserad** (Wizard) | `wizard` | `PromptWizardModalV2` | 5-step guided questionnaire that builds a detailed prompt |
| **Kategori** (Templates) | `category` | `TemplateGallery` | Browse template categories, pick a starting point |
| **Audit** | `audit` | `SiteAuditSection` + `AuditModal` | Analyze an existing website URL, show improvement suggestions |
| **Fritext** (Freeform) | `freeform` | `PromptInput` | Type a free-text description directly |

All 4 modes lead to the **builder** via `/builder?buildMethod=<mode>&...`

### Builder (`/builder`)

The main workspace where the user iterates on their site:
- Left panel: chat interface (prompt, AI responses, version history)
- Right panel: live preview (iframe showing the demoUrl from v0)
- Header: model selection, deploy button, project settings

### Admin (`/admin`)

Internal dashboard with tabs: Database, Environment, Analytics, Prompts.

## Key concepts

### Template vs scaffold vs Vercel template

These three concepts are different and should NOT be mixed:

| Term | Swedish label | Meaning | Scope |
|------|---------------|---------|-------|
| **Template** | `kategori-mall` or `mallkategori` | Our current user-facing template/category system in sajtmaskin. Used for inspiration, filtering, and starting points in the builder UI. | Product/UI concept |
| **Scaffold** | `grundmall`, `startmall`, or `hemsidemall` | An internal, code-level starter project that the LLM modifies instead of generating everything from scratch. Usually 3-8 files with working navigation, footer, layout, and components. | Internal engine concept |
| **Vercel Template** | `extern Vercel-template` | A public template/starter repo from [vercel.com/templates](https://vercel.com/templates). These are references or source material for building our own scaffolds, not something we should fetch live during every generation. | External ecosystem concept |
| **Multi-tenant** | `delad plattform` | One codebase / one deployment serving many tenants with different data/domains. Best term for the sajtmaskin app itself. | Hosting architecture concept |
| **Multi-project** | `separata kundprojekt` | One isolated Vercel project per customer/app. Best term for generated user sites and deploy targets. | Hosting architecture concept |

Preferred terminology:
- In product copy for users: say **`hemsidemall`** or **`startmall`**
- In engine/code discussions: say **`scaffold`** or **`starter scaffold`**
- When referring to Vercel's public library: explicitly say **`Vercel template`**

Important rule:
- Do NOT call our internal scaffolds just `templates` without qualifier, since sajtmaskin already uses `templates` for another concept.
- Do NOT use `multi-tenant` or `multi-project` as if they were template concepts. They describe hosting/deployment architecture, not content/category selection.

### Build method (`BuildMethod`)

How the user entered the builder. One of:
`wizard` | `category` | `audit` | `freeform` | `kostnadsfri`

### Build intent (`BuildIntent`)

What the user wants to build:
- `website` - standard multi-page website (default)
- `app` - interactive app with logic/flows
- `template` - compact 1-2 page template

### Project

A sajtmaskin project that groups chats, versions, and deployments together.
Stored in our database. Has an `appProjectId` (ours) and optionally a
`v0ProjectId` (on v0's side).

### Chat

A conversation with v0. Each chat produces versions. Mapped to a v0 chat ID.

### Version

A snapshot of generated code from a single v0 response. Has a `demoUrl`
(live preview on v0's servers) and files (the actual React/Next.js code).

### demoUrl

A temporary preview URL returned by v0 Platform API after code generation.
Hosted on `*.vusercontent.net`. Used directly in the builder's iframe preview.
Not the same as a deployed site.

### Deployment

When the user clicks "Deploy", we:
1. Fetch the version's files from v0
2. Process images (upload to Vercel Blob if needed)
3. Create a Vercel deployment via Vercel REST API
4. Return a permanent URL on the user's Vercel project

## Preview: why iframe and not always sandboxed?

The builder preview uses a plain **iframe** with the v0 `demoUrl` as source.
This is fast and simple - v0 hosts the preview, no local build needed.

The **Sandbox** (`@vercel/sandbox` via `SandboxModal`) is a separate, manual
tool for running code in an isolated server environment. It exists because:

- The demoUrl preview is **read-only** - it shows what v0 generated but cannot
  run custom server logic, access env vars, or connect to databases
- Sandbox gives **full runtime control** - Node.js process, env vars, npm install
- Sandbox is slower to start and costs more resources

So the default flow is: demoUrl in iframe (instant, free, good enough for
visual preview). Sandbox is opt-in for when the user needs to test server-side
behavior before deploying.

After deployment, the site runs as a real Vercel deployment with full
server capabilities.

## Builder picker components

The builder toolbar exposes four picker dialogs, each in its own file:

| Component | File | What it does |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| `UiElementPicker` | `UiElementPicker.tsx` | Browse and insert shadcn/ui blocks & components |
| `ThemePicker` | `ThemePicker.tsx` | Select a design theme (OKLch palette) |
| `TemplatePicker` | `TemplatePicker.tsx` | Pick a starting template category |
| `AiElementPicker` | `AiElementPicker.tsx` | Insert AI-powered UI elements (hero, pricing, etc.) |

## Naming conventions in code

| Concept | Variable/type name | Example value |
|---------|-------------------|---------------|
| Our project ID | `appProjectId` | `"proj_abc123"` |
| v0 project ID | `v0ProjectId` | `"prj_xyz"` |
| v0 chat ID | `v0ChatId` / `chatId` | `"chat_abc"` |
| Preview URL | `demoUrl` / `currentDemoUrl` | `"https://v0-abc.vusercontent.net"` |
| Deployed URL | `url` (in deployment) | `"https://my-site.vercel.app"` |
| Entry mode | `buildMethod` | `"wizard"` |
| Build type | `buildIntent` | `"website"` |
